  "prompt": "How can I start an online library?",
  "response": "Here are steps to start an online library:\n\n1. Planning Phase\n- Define your library's purpose and target audience\n- Choose a specific genre or focus (academic, fiction, non-fiction)\n- Determine your business model (free, subscription, pay-per-book)\n\n2. Legal Considerations\n- Research copyright laws\n- Obtain necessary permissions for digital book distribution\n- Establish terms of service and usage policies\n\n3. Technical Infrastructure\n- Select a suitable platform (WordPress, custom website)\n- Choose a hosting service\n- Implement secure user authentication\n- Create a database for book catalog\n- Develop search and browsing features\n\n4. Content Acquisition\n- Partner with publishers\n- Use public domain books\n- Obtain digital publishing rights\n- Consider creating original content\n\n5. Technical Requirements\n- Develop responsive website design\n- Implement secure payment systems\n- Create digital book viewer/reader\n- Enable download/streaming options\n- Ensure mobile compatibility\n\n6. Marketing and Promotion\n- Create social media presence\n- Use SEO strategies\n- Develop email marketing campaigns\n- Offer initial promotions/free trials\n\n7. Additional Considerations\n- Implement user reviews/ratings\n- Create recommendation systems\n- Develop customer support channels\n\nConsider consulting legal and technical professionals during implementation.",
